pageTitle: CHS makes it three straight in Citizens Bank/CU Classic | CKNJ.com
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {19073=What a difference a couple of weeks have made for the Campbellsville High boys’ basketball program. After a Friday, Dec. 17 loss at Marion County, Eagles’ head coach Tim Davis called a 7 a.m. Saturday practice. CHS played better, not great, to go 2-1 in the T.J. Samson Hospital Holiday Classic at Metcalfe County on Dec. 20-22.
